Author: Tara11
Title: [ANN][ICO-OVER] CoinStarter Successfully Raised $8,515,463.52 🚀 🚀 🚀 🚀
Body: An update from our CEO. CoinStarter is off to a great start, and we’re busy with the new design, layout and software upgrades of our new platform.  We’re also adding some new social features which will further connect our community. With many of these new changes, we’re moving our launch date to May 21, 2018.   We believe more than ever that the opportunities in the coming year for our ecosystem to grow and flourish are truly unlimited.  We’ve begun searching for new additional talent to help us implement our ongoing business model and our new software initiatives. Yes, we’re hiring!  Shortly after the conclusion of our ICO, we kept our word and launched the STAC on all the exchanges that we initially promised.  It has been only a month since our ICO ended and we will continue to be proactive in listing with more exchanges as opportunities present themselves.  Our goal is to grow STAC as a real utility to serve all our future products and services.  We don't think in the short term but the long game.  So, to update you on our Businefy software, we have over 2000 registered users and growing daily.  Businefy is already a fantastic product, but our goal is to continue developing the software for the business enterprise sector.  We see massive adoption in this area for blockchain-as-a-Service (BaaS) in the coming years.  We’re super excited about what we can innovate with Businefy.  This space is going to be big!  On another note, over the last few weeks, there’s been a lot of noise and differing opinions in the crypto space.  Because of these news reports, there seems to be a lack of clarity relating to ICOs by regulatory bodies around the world, so we have a full top-down legal analysis underway to make sure all our software products relating to ICOs are compliant.  We’ll make changes to our software if necessary to seek the approval of our legal team.  We’re confident this process won’t hinder our business model but make us stronger.  Now concerning our Roadmap, the dates are always tentative and not absolute.  As a fact, goal dates on a roadmap are a general target and should not be considered definitive.  As a software company, we aim to beat or come close to the date projections we’ve given.  We’re as motivated as anyone to launch our software updates rapidly, as long as it achieves our objectives. We, therefore, are aiming to launch our new platform May 21, 2018.  Please note, that our product development division has already begun and you’ll see some new products when we launch our new platform, and this will continue in the coming year.  After all, we love innovation!  Again, our entire team is committed to executing our vision in 2018 and beyond!   Cheers, Cornell Holloway

Body: I think the answer is yes, you need to enter your mew address on the provided column on their site before the specified date, otherwise it'll be gone, at least that's what I van conclude from the post.  I had some that I don't remember how much, but I know it's plenty as I am one of those who signed up on the first batch of airdrop. Unfortunately, I didn't put any address before the deadline as I don't think I had ever receive any announcement. And even if they did informed me via an email (lest it be via twitter or telegram as it'll be even more unfair because such announcement can easily be missed), a 10 days window seems too short, especially if we compare them to the duration of "we will inform you once your token is ready for transfer" (or something close to that) message that appears for months on their page.  This is what happened to me, I waited for them to give a more clear instructions on which address can be used as the receiving address, hence I left the address field blank. And I missed the info, and now my balance is... void?

Author: Pali
Title: [ANN][ICO-OVER] CoinStarter Successfully Raised $8,515,463.52 🚀 🚀 🚀 🚀
Body: Who is Pali? I’m into crypto for a while and love to support amazing projects like Coinstarter. To contribute to projects that will change the world. You can find me on reddit and telegram as @cryptomatthias. And @matt (with avatar of myself) on slack. I’m here to help. You can PM me anytime for more details as to what projects I work on.   WHY SO LATE? We wanted to be sure we weren't rushing our message. We want to put out a quality post that covered the foundation of what CoinStarter is all about  HEAVY SITE GRAPHICS Thank you for your input! We're working hard on simplifying the elements surfaced on our website, however our top priority has been to get our platform right.    Why was not mention of this pre ICO before its only a few hours before it ends !! Any official word ?    We're so sorry this was the case. We did make sure to post to Facebook and Twitter, but please let us know if you're not seeing it.     Do the coinstarter box (curated ico coins) only come from ico's starting on coinstarter?  What are some examples of coins that have been delivered via coinstarter box already?  Yes, (I was told they can come from others by Cornell - Joshakatz)  We have coins submitted and many projects, Coinstarter will choose the best out of them and release them as soon as BOX launches, March 2018 is the plan.    I thoroughly went through their team roster and linkedin profiles. No signs of forged accounts and a lot of them have activity from years ago. The team seems pretty credible to me.  Interestingly.. you'll notice that they don't have a marketing strategist  Grin That might explain the current marketing fiasco  Also, has anyone seen this video? I found it on a couple team members' LinkedIn profiles.  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pd-xpzqmcVc  Hi pocketart! It's great to see folks researching and doing their homework on CoinStarter.  We've recently begun pulling resources together to bring a unified brand message and vision to our platform. This goes for videos, banners for ad placement and social marketing and, ultimately, the website. Rest assured that everything is coming together, but we love input from our community and especially those just recently interested in what we're up to.  Keep it coming!
